column4: Hello my wine is not working can someone help me get it to work correctly?
any idea of why it may have done that?

what exactly is it doing/not doing, does typing in wine on the terminal print usage remarks for wine? does typing winecfg bring up the wine configuration, could you have possibly installed a package dependant on the "wine" package and had the wine1.2 package installed and had your previous wine install get overwritten?
I try to reinstall it and I get the following error

This error could be caused by required additional software packages which are missing or not installable. Futhermore there could be a conflict between software packages which are not allowed to be installed at the same time.
The problem just occured after looking threw a forum to get my DVD's to work with vlc media player
I'm not certain but you must have installed a package that requires something that conflicts with a package wine requires
wait i think this is what did it sudo apt-get install libdvdcss2
how do i get rid of sudo apt-get install libdvdcss2
type libdvdcss2 in the search box on synaptic
command to uninstall? don't care if it breaks vlc dvd's
or you can do it via command line sudo apt-get remove libdvdcss2
nope same error I will have to look into more :(
well actually you know any program that will get my ipod to work without wine?
